This paper proposes a novel deep learning paradigm using differential Gaussian process flows, which is a combination of deep learning and Gaussian processes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. Additionally, the paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are related to machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of stochastic differential equations (SDEs) in the proposed method, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and numerical analysis (cs.NE). Finally, the paper compares the proposed method with other deep learning models, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
